other_tests.findings: Gallbladder is seen full of stones with a thickened wall without evidence of significant pericholecystic hepatic enhancement; no evidence of intrahepatic bile duct dilatation; CBD is not dilated; anatomic variant with an aberrant right posterior duct draining into the common hepatic duct; pancreas is of normal size and intensity without evidence of peripancreatic edema; small amount of periduodenal edema around the second and third portion of the duodenum.
